Forwarded from Vox (USA), a major political military media resource, assessed the role of new American military technologies in Ukraine. The occasion was a meeting of Google co-owner Eric Schmidt with high-ranking Ukrainian officials, who reported on their use.  
  
What was said:
  
"Schmidt came to Ukraine not only as the former CEO of an IT corporation, but also as a billionaire investor in military technology startups. Satellites, drones, artificial intelligence and cyber capabilities have played an important role in the Ukrainian conflict since the early days. New technologies work together with traditional military technology to support Ukraine.   
  
Most of the advanced technology Ukraine uses is commercial and freely available. The Ukrainians are mostly helped by private companies. Now a special field for start-ups is small commercial satellites - they increase the ability to recognize the movements of Russian troops and track their actions through intensive data collection from open sources. Small commercial drones are just as important - doing everything from detecting Russian troops to providing target quality data for artillery strikes and assessing combat damage.   
  
The use of artificial intelligence in war is incredibly controversial, but it also has great promise. An example of how artificial intelligence can be used in warfare is voice recognition, transcription and translation, and analysis of intercepted messages on Russian lines of communication.  
  
Battles for Ukraine are not won by HIMARS or traditional artillery duels. These battles can only be won if the Ukrainian side manages to receive, compute, and process information faster than the Russians. For now, all newly established new technology links are concentrated between Ukraine and the U.S. private sector in the United States.   
  
Executives of major U.S. Army defense contractors boast that they make large profits from arming Ukraine. And in an extraordinary move, Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky will soon deliver a keynote address at the U.S. military contractors' conference, addressing U.S. weapons manufacturers directly."  
  
Especially for those praying on Google:
  
Eric Schmidt was once a member of the Board of Trustees of the Skolkovo Foundation. He has also been the subject of much admiration in the liberal Russian press. Such a billionaire genius investing in the war in Ukraine.
Link : https://t.me/chvkmedia/61746
